**File**: `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775348217446-t7xr2l/tests/utils.test.ts`

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { processItems, sum } from "../src/utils.js";

describe("processItems", () => {
  it("should process all items in the array", () => {
    expect(processItems(["hello", "world", "foo"])).toEqual([
      "HELLO",
      "WORLD",
      "FOO",
    ]);
  });

  it("should handle a single item", () => {
    expect(processItems(["test"])).toEqual(["TEST"]);
  });

  it("should handle two items", () => {
    expect(processItems(["a", "b"])).toEqual(["A", "B"]);
  });

  it("should return empty array for empty input", () => {
    expect(processItems([])).toEqual([]);
  });
});

describe("sum", () => {
  it("should sum numbers correctly", () => {
    expect(sum([1, 2, 3])).toBe(6);
  });

  it("should return 0 for empty array", () => {
    expect(sum([])).toBe(0);
  });
});
```

**Tests 1, 2, and 3 will fail** with the current buggy code:
- Test 1: Returns `["HELLO", "WORLD"]` instead of `["HELLO", "WORLD", "FOO"]`
- Test 2: Returns `[]` instead of `["TEST"]` (single item is the last item)
- Test 3: Returns `["A"]` instead of `["A", "B"]` (second item is the last item)
- Test 4: Passes (empty array has no last item to skip)

